ce:section.ce:para:
By SEM analysis the morphology of the obtained N- and S-CDs (Fig. 1
                        ) could be visualized; the obtained images exhibit spherical shape and different degree of aggregations for N-CDs (Fig. 1B) and S-CDs (Fig. 1C) compared with the raw CDs (Fig. 1A). This fact can be explained by the different surface charge of modified carbon dots; S-CDs surface is populated by a higher concentration of sulphonic (R–SO3
                        -) groups and N-CDs by amide/amine (-CONH2/-CNH2) protonable groups.
